{
  "mitigation_currently_implemented": "Apply ICMP rate limiting rules on the FORWARD chain of the Floor4-FW firewall, targeting the source IP of the compromised host (192.168.120.3) and limiting ICMP echo-request packets with a rate such as 10 per second with burst of 20 to effectively throttle flood traffic passing through the firewall",
  "comments": "On the Floor4-FW firewall, I implemented ICMP echo-request (ping) rate limiting specifically for traffic originating from the compromised host (192.168.120.3) on the FORWARD chain. The rule allows 10 ICMP echo-request packets per second with a burst of 20 and drops additional packets. This targets the ongoing ICMP flood attack by throttling excessive ping traffic passing through the firewall, reducing impact while allowing normal traffic. This respects the constraint of keeping the compromised host and attacker active while mitigating the attack.",
  "device_identifier": "Floor4-FW",
  "commands": [
    "iptables -A FORWARD -p icmp --icmp-type echo-request -s 192.168.120.3 -m limit --limit 10/sec --limit-burst 20 -j ACCEPT",
    "iptables -A FORWARD -p icmp --icmp-type echo-request -s 192.168.120.3 -j DROP"
  ]
}
